    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This investment-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD showcases the pinnacle of rotary engineering. Powered by the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged engine, it maintains factory-spec compression and a flawless boost transition across the primary and secondary turbines. The 5-speed manual gearbox is paired with a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal power delivery through the rear wheels. The lightweight chassis features double-wishbone suspension at all four corners, offering the precise 50/50 weight distribution the FD is legendary for. Every mechanical component, from the complex vacuum-controlled solenoid 'rat's nest' to the four-piston braking system, operates with surgical precision. This is a zero-compromise, mechanically pristine example of Japanese performance history.",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 39
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
